Matthew Gray Gubler is an Emmy award-winning actor, director, comedian, painter, producer and #1 New York Times Bestselling author/illustrator from Las Vegas, Nevada. While studying film directing at NYU he interned for Wes Anderson who gave him his first acting role as Bill Murray's loyal intern "Nico" in The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou.
